org.xlattice.corexml.om

Class Element

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.xlattice.corexml.om.Node
      • org.xlattice.corexml.om.Holder
        • org.xlattice.corexml.om.Element

  • public class Element
extends Holder
    An XML element node. This implementation specifies the element in terms of its prefix and name.

    XXX Need to consider whether to store the Namespace (uri) rather than the prefix; could resolve prefix in the constructor. This decision will have consequences.

    In this implementation an element always has its own attribute list.

    Author:
    Jim Dixon
